---
/**
 * /spike/appshell/dome/ — second half of the AppShell persistence spike.
 *
 * Pairs with /spike/appshell/ — same AppShell, different routeName, the
 * starfield singleton lerps the camera + hue when the route changes.
 */
import AppShell from '../../../../components/AppShell.astro';
---

<AppShell title="P31 spike — AppShell dome" routeName="dome">
  <h1>Track 2.5 spike — AppShell dome</h1>
  <p>
    Camera pulled deeper. Hue shifted toward coral. If you got here without a
    flash, the canvas survived navigation. Press <em>home</em> to send the
    camera back. The lerp should take ~600&nbsp;ms either way.
  </p>
  <nav class="p31-spike-nav" aria-label="Spike routes">
    <a href="/spike/appshell/">home</a>
    <a href="/spike/appshell/dome/" aria-current="page">dome</a>
  </nav>
  <p>
    With <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code> the lerp half-life is
    still 600&nbsp;ms (visually a brief soft snap rather than instant), kept
    deliberately so the persistence test is detectable in headless Chromium.
    Reduced-motion in production routes will use a 0&nbsp;ms snap.
  </p>
</AppShell>
